title: All Australians accounted for in Iraq: Downer (AFP)
description: AFP - Australia has accounted for all its nationals known to be working in Iraq following a claim by a radical Islamic group to have kidnapped two Australians, Foreign Affairs Minister Alexander Downer said.

title: A trio of television technologies
description: AUSTRALIANS went into a television-buying frenzy the run-up to the Athens Olympics, suggesting that as a nation we could easily have scored a gold medal for TV purchasing.

title: National Foods posts increased net profit
description: Australia #39;s biggest supplier of fresh milk, National Foods, has posted a net profit of \$68.7 million, an increase of 14 per cent on last financial year.

title: Australia's leader wins 4th term
description: SYDNEY -- Prime Minister John Howard of Australia, a key US ally and supporter of the Iraq war, celebrated his election win over opposition Labor after voters enjoying the fruits of a strong economy gave him another term.

title: Cricket: Aussies dominate India
description: Australia tighten their grip on the third Test and the series after dominating India on day two in Nagpur.

title: Woman believed to be 1st to walk around Australia strides back to hometown (Canadian Press)
description: Canadian Press - MELBOURNE, Australia (AP) - A 36-year-old businesswoman was believed to be the first woman to walk around Australia on Friday after striding into her hometown of Melbourne to complete her 16,700-kilometre trek in 365 days.

title: Australia clinches series sweep
description: Australia completed an emphatic Test series sweep over New Zealand with a 213-run win Tuesday, prompting a caution from Black Caps skipper Stephen Fleming for other cricket captains around the globe.

title: US buy spurs registrar #39;s share surge
description: Australia #39;s Computershare has agreed to buy EquiServe of the United States for US\$292 million (\$423 million), making it the largest US share registrar and driving its shares up by a third.

title: Springboks targets scrum
description: THE South Africans have called the Wallabies scrum cheats as a fresh round of verbal warfare opened in the Republic last night.

title: Man tried for UK student's murder
description: The trial of a man accused of murdering York backpacker Caroline Stuttle begins in Australia.
